entropy.configuration

Class SimpleManagedElementSet<E extends entropy.configuration.ManagedElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<E>
          • entropy.configuration.SimpleManagedElementSet<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    entropy.configuration.ManagedElementSet<E>, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>, RandomAccess

    public class SimpleManagedElementSet<E extends entropy.configuration.ManagedElement>
extends ArrayList<E>
implements entropy.configuration.ManagedElementSet<E>, Cloneable
    Basic implementation of a ManagedElementSet. add(),addAll(), contains(), , get(), , set() operations are performed in an almost constant time. remove(), removeAll() operations are in a constant time if the element is not in the set. O(n) otherwise
    Author:
    Fabien Hermenier
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
